== 人口历史 ==
===人口===
根据现代分析，人类在大约公元前七万年遭遇了[[种群瓶颈|种群瓶颈]]。起因可能是印尼[[苏门达腊岛|苏门达腊岛]]北部的[[多峇巨灾理论|多峇湖大型火山爆发]]造成的巨灾所影响。从那时起，世界总人口长期停滞在一百万左右，大家都通过[[狩猎采集|狩猎采集]]为生，而这种生存方法使得人口没有条件快速增长。这一状况一直持续到公元前一万一千年，人们开始发展[[农业|农业]]为止。在此之前，世界人口从未超过1,500万人。<ref>Luc-Normand Tellier (2009). "''[http://books.google.com/books?id=cXuCjDbxC1YC&pg=PA26&dq&hl=en#v=onepage&q=&f=false Urban world history: an economic and geographical perspective]''". PUQ. p.26. ISBN 978-2-7605-1588-8</ref>

当人们开始大规模发展农业后，世界人口增长速度有所加快。公元前8000年全世界有人口五百万人；公元1年全世界有大约两亿人，其中[[汉朝|汉朝]]占有六千万人以上；<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.worldometers.info/world-population/ | title=Current World Population | publisher=Worldometers | date=2012-11-21 | accessdate=2012-11-21 | archive-date=2019-05-14 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190514021234/https://www.worldometers.info/world-population/ | dead-url=no }}</ref>而到公元2世纪，[[罗马帝国|罗马帝国]]也拥有了六千万以上的人口。<ref>"[http://www.tulane.edu/~august/H303/handouts/Population.htm Population estimates of the Roman Empire] {{Wayback|url=http://www.tulane.edu/~august/H303/handouts/Population.htm |date=20150826083011 }}", Dr. Kenneth W. Harl</ref>

然而，世界人口的增长又因为瘟疫、战争等影响而有所波动。以欧洲为例，[[查士丁尼大瘟疫|查士丁尼大瘟疫]]使得八世纪欧洲的人口比公元541年减少了大约一半。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://science.nationalgeographic.com/science/health-and-human-body/human-diseases/plague-article.html |title=Plague, Plague Information, Black Death Facts, News, Photos |publisher=National Geographic |accessdate=2008-11-03 |archive-date=2013-06-26 |archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/6HfrvlPBO?url=http://science.nationalgeographic.com/science/health-and-human-body/human-diseases/plague-article.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>随后欧洲的人口又有所增长，到1340年，欧洲大约有七千万人。<ref>"[http://www.britannica.com/EBchecked/topic/195896/history-of-Europe/276190/Demographic-and-agricultural-growth#ref=ref994290 History of Europe – Demographic and agricultural growth] {{Wayback|url=http://www.britannica.com/EBchecked/topic/195896/history-of-Europe/276190/Demographic-and-agricultural-growth#ref=ref994290 |date=20121220154316 }}". Encyclopædia Britannica.</ref>14世纪主要发生在欧洲的[[黑死病|黑死病]]又使得世界人口从1340年的大约4.5亿，减少到1400年大约3.5至3.75亿。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.census.gov/ipc/www/worldhis.html |title=Historical Estimates of World Population |publisher=Census.gov |accessdate=2008-11-03 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110102201303/http://www.census.gov/ipc/www/worldhis.html |archive-date=2011-01-02 |dead-url=yes }}</ref>欧洲随后花了约200年的时间来恢复到1340年时的人口水平。<ref>"[http://www.time.com/time/world/article/0,8599,2050585,00.html A Distant Mirror] {{Wayback|url=http://www.time.com/time/world/article/0,8599,2050585,00.html |date=20080725005418 }}". TIME Europe. July 17, 2000, VOL. 156 NO. 3</ref>而另一个人口大国中国，由于改朝换代的原因，人口也经历了巨幅波动。根据估计，1393年中国大约有6,500万人，比1200年的1.23亿减少了约一半。主要是[[宋朝|宋朝]]至[[元朝|元朝]]长期发生战争的原因。<ref>Horst R. Thieme (2003). "''[http://books.google.com/books?id=cHcjnkrMweYC&pg=PA285&dq&hl=en#v=onepage&q=&f=false Mathematics in population biology]''". Princeton University Press. p.285. ISBN 978-0-691-09291-1</ref><ref>Graziella Caselli, Gillaume Wunsch, Jacques Vallin (2005). "''[http://books.google.com/books?id=nmgNXoiAiU4C&pg=RA2-PA34&dq&hl=en#v=onepage&q=&f=false Demography: Analysis and Synthesis, Four Volume Set: A Treatise in Population]''". Academic Press. p.34. ISBN 978-0-12-765660-1</ref>1368年[[明朝|明朝]]建立时中国的人口大约是6,000万人。到1644年明朝灭亡时，人口增长到约1.5亿。<ref>"[http://afe.easia.columbia.edu/special/china_1750_demographic.htm Qing China's Internal Crisis: Land Shortage, Famine, Rural Poverty] {{Wayback|url=http://afe.easia.columbia.edu/special/china_1750_demographic.htm |date=20110708082757 }}". Asia for Educators, Columbia University.</ref> 

英国的人口在1650年达到560万人。比1500年的260万有所增加。<ref>"[http://www.britannica.com/EBchecked/topic/195896/history-of-Europe/58335/Demographics#ref=ref310375 History of Europe – Demographics] {{Wayback|url=http://www.britannica.com/EBchecked/topic/195896/history-of-Europe/58335/Demographics#ref=ref310375 |date=20130723052625 }}". Encyclopædia Britannica.</ref>十六世纪欧洲掀起的殖民潮也为世界人口增长做出了贡献，因为殖民者往往会将殖民地较为先进的农作物（例如[[玉米|玉米]]、[[红薯|红薯]]）带到其它地区推广以增加粮食产量。<ref>"[http://afe.easia.columbia.edu/china/geog/population.htm China's Population: Readings and Maps] {{Wayback|url=http://afe.easia.columbia.edu/china/geog/population.htm |date=20110719173803 }}". Columbia University, East Asian Curriculum Project.</ref><ref>[http://www.learnnc.org/lp/editions/nchist-twoworlds/1866 The Columbian Exchange] {{Wayback|url=http://www.learnnc.org/lp/editions/nchist-twoworlds/1866 |date=20110812142620 }}. The University of North Carolina.</ref><ref>[http://researchnews.osu.edu/archive/suprtubr.htm Super-Sized Cassava Plants May Help Fight Hunger In Africa] {{Wayback|url=http://researchnews.osu.edu/archive/suprtubr.htm |date=20131208143623 }}. The Ohio State University</ref><ref>"''[http://books.google.com/books?id=zOm0iqkRsYEC&pg=PA242&dq&hl=en#v=onepage&q=&f=false Albert Schweitzer: a biography]''". James Brabazon (2000). Syracuse University Press. p.242. ISBN 978-0-8156-0675-8</ref>

1500年的美洲（包括北美和南美）人口约有五千万至一亿人。<ref>J. N. Hays (1998). "''[http://books.google.com/books?id=iMHmn9c38QgC&pg=PA72&dq&hl=en#v=onepage&q=&f=false The burdens of disease: epidemics and human response in western history.]''". p 72. ISBN 978-0-8135-2528-0</ref>哥伦布发现美洲大陆前的北美洲约有两百万至一千八百万人。<ref>"[http://www.sciencemag.org/cgi/content/short/268/5217/1601 Microchronology and Demographic Evidence Relating to the Size of Pre-Columbian North American Indian Populations]". ''[[Science_(journal)|Science]]''.</ref>然而，欧洲人却把一些当地土著从未遇到过的传染病也带到了北美，由于当地人还没有建立起这些疾病的免疫力，估计当时的北美原住民有90%是因为感染上传染病而死。<ref>Arthur C. Aufderheide, Conrado Rodríguez-Martín, Odin Langsjoen (1998). "''[http://books.google.com/books?id=qubTdDk1H3IC&pg=PA205&dq&hl=en#v=onepage&q=&f=false The Cambridge encyclopedia of human paleopathology] {{Wayback|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=qubTdDk1H3IC&pg=PA205&dq&hl=en#v=onepage&q=&f=false|date=20130528191514}}''". [[Cambridge_University_Press|Cambridge University Press]]. p.205. ISBN 978-0-521-55203-5</ref><ref>"[http://www.pbs.org/gunsgermssteel/variables/smallpox.html The Story Of... Smallpox – and other Deadly Eurasian Germs] {{Wayback|url=http://www.pbs.org/gunsgermssteel/variables/smallpox.html |date=20180129120446 }}". Public Broadcasting Service (PBS).</ref><ref>{{Cite book
