随着[[英国农业革命|农业革命]]与[[工业革命|工业革命]]的展开，人们的生活水平提高，死亡率下降，婴儿存活率大幅上升，人均寿命也有所延长。<ref>[http://home.vicnet.net.au/~ozideas/poprus.htm Population crises and cycles in history] {{Wayback|url=http://home.vicnet.net.au/~ozideas/poprus.htm |date=20110405081151 }}. A review of the book ''Population Crises and Population cycles'' by Claire Russell and W.M.S. Russell.</ref>以英国为例，1730-1749年，英国有74.5%的儿童在五岁前即夭折，在1810-1829年，这一数字降为31.8%。<ref name="Buer">Mabel C. Buer, ''Health, Wealth and Population in the Early Days of the Industrial Revolution'', London: George Routledge & Sons, 1926, page 30 ISBN 978-0-415-38218-2</ref><ref>[http://www.bbc.co.uk/history/british/victorians/foundling_01.shtml BBC – History – The Foundling Hospital] {{Wayback|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/history/british/victorians/foundling_01.shtml |date=20111013092142 }}. Published: 2001-05-01.</ref>1700年起欧洲人口开始剧烈上升，到1900年已经达到4亿，比1700年的一亿人翻了四倍。<ref>"[http://www.britannica.com/EBchecked/topic/387301/modernization/12022/Population-change Modernization – Population Change] {{Wayback|url=http://www.britannica.com/EBchecked/topic/387301/modernization/12022/Population-change |date=20090406074344 }}". ''Encyclopædia Britannica''.</ref>而1900年时的欧洲人口占了全世界人口约36%。<ref>Graziella Caselli, Gillaume Wunsch, Jacques Vallin (2005). "''[http://books.google.com/books?id=nmgNXoiAiU4C&pg=RA2-PA42&dq&hl=en#v=onepage&q=&f=false Demography: Analysis and Synthesis, Four Volume Set: A Treatise in Population]''". Academic Press. p.42. ISBN 978-0-12-765660-1</ref>

在19世纪，强制[[人痘接种术|种痘]]已经在西方国家展开，而医疗卫生设备也在这些地方普及开来，西方国家人口增长速度也不断上升。英国的人口更是每五十年便翻一番。<ref>[http://www.bbc.co.uk/history/british/victorians/victorian_medicine_01.shtml BBC – History – Victorian Medicine – From Fluke to Theory] {{Wayback|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/history/british/victorians/victorian_medicine_01.shtml |date=20201108110941 }}. Published: 2002-02-01.</ref><ref>[http://www.independent.co.uk/news/uk/home-news/a-portrait-of-britain-in-2031-395231.html A portrait of Britain in 2031] {{Wayback|url=http://www.independent.co.uk/news/uk/home-news/a-portrait-of-britain-in-2031-395231.html |date=20210319041926 }}. The Independent. October 24, 2007.</ref>1801年，英国有830万人；在1901年，人口增加到3,050万人；而在2006年，则有超过六千万人。<ref>{{cite web |title=The UK population: past, present and future |url=http://www.statistics.gov.uk/downloads/theme_compendia/fom2005/01_FOPM_Population.pdf |format=PDF |publisher=Statistics.gov.uk |accessdate=2009-09-05 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110728130246/http://www.statistics.gov.uk/downloads/theme_compendia/fom2005/01_FOPM_Population.pdf |archivedate=2011-07-28 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/uk_news/5281360.stm | title=UK population breaks through 60m | publisher=BBC | date=2006-08-24 | accessdate=2012-11-24 | archive-date=2022-04-07 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220407213328/http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/uk_news/5281360.stm }}</ref>美国的人口也从1800年的530万增长到1920年的1.06亿。在2010年，美国已经有超过3.07亿人。<ref>{{cite web | url=http://geography.about.com/od/obtainpopulationdata/a/uspop.htm | title=US population through history | publisher=About.com | date=2011-07-21 | accessdate=2012-11-24 | archive-date=2012-01-13 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120113011006/http://geography.about.com/od/obtainpopulationdata/a/uspop.htm | dead-url=no }}</ref>

二十世纪初和中叶的苏联人口经历了较大起伏。由于持续不断的战争，截止到1945年二战结束，苏联丧失了约九千万人。<ref>Mark Harrison (2002). "''[http://books.google.com/books?id=yJcD7_Q_rQ8C&pg=PA167&dq&hl=en#v=onepage&q=&f=false Accounting for War: Soviet Production, Employment, and the Defence Burden, 1940–1945]''". Cambridge University Press. p.167. ISBN 978-0-521-89424-1</ref><ref>Stephen J. Lee (2000). "''[http://books.google.com/books?id=KnvJO9yfvEAC&pg=PA86&dq&hl=en#v=onepage&q=&f=false European dictatorships, 1918–1945]''". Routledge. p.86. ISBN 978-0-415-23046-9</ref>随后苏联的人口平稳增长，但从二十世纪九十年代起，苏联解体后的俄罗斯人口又陷入停滞。2012年俄罗斯有1.43亿，比1991年的1.48亿有所减少，如果人口发展形势不变，到了2050年，更会降到1.07亿。<ref>[http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/worldnews/vladimir-putin/9078672/Vladimir-Putin-vows-to-reverse-Russian-population-decline.html "Vladimir Putin vows to reverse Russian population decline"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/worldnews/vladimir-putin/9078672/Vladimir-Putin-vows-to-reverse-Russian-population-decline.html |date=20220407114753 }}. ''[[The_Daily_Telegraph|The Daily Telegraph]]'', February 13, 2012. Retrieved 2012-04-13.</ref>

第二次世界大战后，由于世界进入相对和平的时期，科技、医疗水平持续改善，许多[[发展中国家|发展中国家]]的人口增长十分迅速。这些国家主要来自亚洲、非洲和拉丁美洲。以中国为例，1850年的[[清朝|清朝]]约有4.3亿人，1953年中国共产党基本完成土地革命时有5.8亿人。尽管战争不断，一百多年间人口还是增长了1.5亿。<ref>[http://www.jstor.org/discover/10.2307/652987?uid=3738032&uid=2460337935&uid=2460338175&uid=2129&uid=2&uid=70&uid=4&uid=83&uid=63&sid=56034385973 "China's demographic evolution 1850–1953 reconsidered" (1978)]. ''The China Quarterly'' via JSTOR. Retrieved 2012-04-13.</ref>从五十年代起，中国的人口也迅猛增长，1982年人口普查显示中国人口超过十亿；现今，中国有超过14亿人口，庞大的人口数迫使中国政府实行了[[计划生育|计划生育]]政策以减缓人口增长。世界第二多人口的印度在1750年约有1.25亿人，1941年达到3.89亿；<ref>[http://www.petersoninstitute.org/publications/chapters_preview/98/1iie2806.pdf "Reintegrating India with the World Economy" (PDF)] {{Wayback|url=http://www.petersoninstitute.org/publications/chapters_preview/98/1iie2806.pdf |date=20120304085740 }}. Peterson Institute for International Economics. 2003. Retrieved November 8, 2012.</ref>而当前印度已经有超过13亿人口。<ref>[https://www.cia.gov/library/publications/the-world-factbook/geos/in.html CIA World Factbook] {{Wayback|url=https://www.cia.gov/library/publications/the-world-factbook/geos/in.html |date=20080611033144 }}. July 2012 estimate. Retrieved 2012-10-21.</ref>印尼[[爪哇|爪哇]]地区的人口从1815年的五百万人升到当前的1.3亿人。<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.britannica.com/EBchecked/topic/301673/Java | title=Java (island, Indonesia) | publisher=Encyclopædia Britannica | accessdate=2012-11-24 | archive-date=2013-07-09 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130709163506/http://www.britannica.com/EBchecked/topic/301673/Java | dead-url=no }}</ref>墨西哥的人口从1900年的1,300万增长到2009年的1.12亿。<ref>"[http://www.migrationinformation.org/Feature/display.cfm?ID=203 From Traitors to Heroes: 100 Years of Mexican Migration Policies] {{Wayback|url=http://www.migrationinformation.org/Feature/display.cfm?ID=203 |date=20110505074111 }}". Jorge Durand, University of Guadalajara. March 2004.</ref>非洲的[[肯尼亚|肯尼亚]]人口也从1920年的290万增长到当前超过3,700万。 <ref>"[http://www.nytimes.com/2008/01/17/opinion/17iht-edheinsohn.1.9292632.html Kenya's Violence: Exploding population] {{Wayback|url=http://www.nytimes.com/2008/01/17/opinion/17iht-edheinsohn.1.9292632.html |date=20210309015744 }}". ''The New York Times''. January 7, 2008. Gunnar Heinsohn</ref>

进入二十一世纪，随着许多发展中国家的经济、教育水平提高，这些国家不约而同地出现了人口增长放缓的迹象。这主要体现在出生率开始下降，并由之而来的[[人口老化|老龄化]]趋势与死亡率上升。在一些发达地区（例如日本、德国），人口已经开始逐渐减少。<ref name="fanghuan">{{cite web | url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/chinese/simp/hi/newsid_3610000/newsid_3619000/3619068.stm | title=人口增长放缓导致世界人口预测下调 | publisher=BBC | date=2004-09-01 | accessdate=2012-11-21 | archive-date=2021-08-05 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210805094733/http://news.bbc.co.uk/chinese/simp/hi/newsid_3610000/newsid_3619000/3619068.stm }}</ref>

=== 人口-{里}-程碑 ===
